  "title": "Freshness fingerprints anchor to named symbols, not just whole-file hash",
  "summary": "Memory freshness was whole file SHA 256, so any edit to a big file like kernel.ts marked every citing packet content stale. Added symbol anchored fingerprints: MemoryPathFingerprint gained optional symbols. memoryPathFin",
  "body": "Memory freshness was whole-file SHA-256, so any edit to a big file like kernel.ts marked every citing packet content-stale. Added symbol-anchored fingerprints: MemoryPathFingerprint gained optional symbols. memoryPathFingerprints now takes anchorText (packet title+summary+body) and records per-symbol content hashes via extractSymbols line spans, but ONLY for symbol names that resolve to exactly one span (extractSymbols recurses into bodies, so generic locals like a loop binding appear many times and must be skipped as ambiguous). fingerprintPathContentChanged is the single content-drift decision: whole-file equal then not changed; else if anchored, stale only when a named symbol span hash changed or the symbol is gone; else whole-file fallback. Wired into staleMemoryReasons, staleCatch, capture, compact, reverify. packetStoredPathFingerprints preserves symbols. Only TS JS extensions anchor. Backward compatible: legacy packets without symbols keep whole-file until reverified.\nVerified by: 346 tests pass incl 4 new anchoring tests",
